cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF 

This paper deals with improving inter-datacenter transfers, which involves network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of multiple forwarding trees and their construction, which falls under the category of distributed systems, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely category. The paper also presents a solution to the problem of partitioning receivers and determining the rate and schedule of flows, which involves system optimization and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper uses simulations to evaluate the proposed solution, which involves data analysis and modeling, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with improving bandwidth usage, which involves performance optimization, making cs.PF (Performance) a possible category.
